Package com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models

Class ServiceProperties.Logging

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models.ServiceProperties.Logging
  • Enclosing class:
    ServiceProperties

    public static class ServiceProperties.Logging
extends java.lang.Object
    This inner class represents the settings for logging on the Queue service of the storage account. These settings include the Storage Analytics version, whether to log delete requests, read requests, or write requests, and a ServiceProperties.RetentionPolicy instance for retention policy settings.

      • isWrite

        public boolean isWrite​()
        Gets a flag indicating whether queue write operations are logged. If this value is true then all requests that write to the Queue service will be logged. These requests include adding a message, updating a message, setting queue metadata, and creating a queue.
        Returns:
        true if queue write operations are logged, otherwise false.

      • setWrite

        public ServiceProperties.Logging setWrite​(boolean write)
        Sets a flag indicating whether queue write operations are logged. If this value is true then all requests that write to the Queue service will be logged. These requests include adding a message, updating a message, setting queue metadata, and creating a queue.
        Parameters:
        write - true to enable logging of queue write operations, otherwise false.
        Returns:
        A reference to this ServiceProperties.Logging instance.

      • isRead

        public boolean isRead​()
        Gets a flag indicating whether queue read operations are logged. If this value is true then all requests that read from the Queue service will be logged. These requests include listing queues, getting queue metadata, listing messages, and peeking messages.
        Returns:
        true if queue read operations are logged, otherwise false.
